; form-cli-ask.fk - the form-cli ASK verb, native on the fkwu walker.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/str-byte-at.fk form-stdlib/sha256.fk form-stdlib/hex.fk
; preludes: form-stdlib/text-tokenize.fk form-stdlib/rag-embed.fk
; preludes: form-stdlib/rag-index-codec.fk form-stdlib/rag-retrieve.fk
; preludes: form-stdlib/rag-ask.fk
; preludes: form-stdlib/ask-cost-receipt.fk form-stdlib/ask-native-lane.fk
;
; The local answer starts with the body: the one-shot CLI stages the question, then fkwu reads the
; staged query and healed RAG JSONL index directly. It does not call Ollama, localhost:11434,
; http-fetch, host-exec, or a shell.
;
; WHAT CHANGED ON 2026-07-21, AND WHY THE OLD HEADER HAD TO GO. Until today this file said: "Full
; prose generation over GGUF weights on the fkwu + Metal model lane is a separate composition cell;
; until that lane is wired end-to-end, this verb returns an attributed grounded cell instead of
; pretending a host LLM is the local oracle." That refusal was exactly right, and it was written
; against a CONDITION — "until that lane is wired end-to-end". The condition became false at 14:14
; today: metal_first_token.sh generates real llama3.2:3b tokens from real weights, full width, through
; kernels the body emitted, and passes 13 gates doing it. Nothing tells a comment when the world moves
; under it, so the verb went on returning a RAG cell for three hours after it no longer had to. The
; honest repair is to make the sentence TRUE, not to soften it — so the model lane is now wired, and
; the refusal survives verbatim in `fca-grounded-answer` as a NAMED lane rather than as the only one.
;
; TWO LANES, AND THE VERB ALWAYS SAYS WHICH ONE SPOKE.
;   metal-gguf-native   real llama3.2:3b prose, generated form-native off the resident quantized blob
;                       (ask-native-lane.fk; carrier form/native/metal/metal_ask.sh). Every answer
;                       carries the model, the blob, the question it is bound to, and a cost receipt
;                       in which every cost appears DECLARED (a bound derived from the model's own
;                       shape, before the run) and MEASURED, with the measured value as a fraction of
;                       its bound.
;   fkwu-rag-grounded   the attributed grounded cell out of the healed local index. NOT a degraded
;                       mode and NOT deleted: when the question wants provenance rather than prose, a
;                       grounded `@p.l.t.i` cell is the better answer, and when the model lane is
;                       unavailable it is the honest one.
; The lanes are never blended and never guessed at. `fca-lane-of` reports the lane that WILL answer
; before it answers, and every returned body carries `local-lane:` on its own line. A caller that
; mistook a 3-billion-parameter generation for a retrieved cell, or the reverse, would be misled about
; the only thing that matters here, so the fallback is announced with its REASON attached
; (`native-lane:absent`, `...:question-not-bound`, ...) rather than taken silently.
;
; THE RADIUS THIS FILE SPEAKS FOR (corpus row 826, aporon). It speaks for CHOOSING between the two
; lanes and for attributing what it returns. It does not speak for the arithmetic behind either — the
; native lane's tokens are gated by form/native/metal/metal_first_token.sh, the grounded lane's
; provenance by rag-ask.fk — and it deliberately does not speak for the model lane being FRESH beyond
; question identity: see ask-native-lane.fk's named BLOB-SHA256 gap.
;
; Kin: ask-native-lane.fk (anl-* — the native lane door and its question binding), ask-cost-receipt.fk
; (acr-* — declared/measured costs), rag-ask.fk (ra-* — the grounded lane), form-cli-ask-gate.fk
; (fca-ask-result — the posterior sufficiency gate this feeds), form-cli.fk (the verb table).
;
; Proven by: form-stdlib/tests/form-cli-ask-band.fk, form-stdlib/tests/ask-cost-receipt-band.fk

(do
    ; The lane that WILL answer this question, asked before answering it. A caller can route on this
    ; without paying for the answer, and a test can assert the routing without a GPU on the host.
    (defn fca-native-lane () (anl-lane-name))
    (defn fca-rag-lane () (anl-fallback-lane-name))
    (defn fca-lane-of (question)
        (if (eq (anl-ready? question) 1) (fca-native-lane) (fca-rag-lane)))
    ; kept: callers and receipts that predate the model lane ask for "the local lane" with no question
    ; in hand. The grounded lane is the answer to that, because it is the one that is always there.
    (defn fca-local-lane () (fca-rag-lane))

    ; ── the grounded lane, unchanged in meaning and now NAMED as one lane among two ───────────────
    ; THE MISS CARRIES ITS LANE TOO. Until 2026-07-22 the grounded-miss branch returned a bare
    ; bracketed sentence with no `local-lane:` on it — the one shape in this whole file that answered
    ; without saying who answered. It looked harmless because a miss is not prose and could not be
    ; mistaken for a generation. It was not harmless: a caller that routes on `local-lane:` reads a
    ; miss as an answer from NO lane, which is the one thing that never happens here, and the ask
    ; verb's whole discipline is that the lane is never absent from what it hands back.
    (defn fca-grounded-answer (question)
        (do (let grounded (ra-grounded question))
        (if (str_eq grounded "grounded:miss")
            "[ask: local fkwu RAG index has no grounded hit]\nlocal-lane:fkwu-rag-grounded\nsynthesis-lane:fkwu-rag-grounded"
            (str_concat grounded
                "\nlocal-lane:fkwu-rag-grounded\nsynthesis-lane:fkwu-rag-grounded"))))

    ; A fallback that does not say it fell back is a fallback that lies by omission. When the native
    ; lane declines, its reason travels with the grounded answer.
    (defn fca-fallback-answer (question)
        (str_concat (fca-grounded-answer question)
            (str_concat "\ndeclined:" (anl-refusal question))))

    ; ── the verb ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    (defn fca-ask (question)
        (if (eq (anl-ready? question) 1)
            (anl-answer question)
            (fca-fallback-answer question)))

    ; `model` names WHICH model was asked for. The native lane carries exactly one model — the blob
    ; the carrier mapped — so a request for a different one must not be answered by it wearing that
    ; name. Asking for the model the lane actually holds routes natively; anything else is grounded.
    (defn fca-ask-model (model question)
        (if (str_eq model (anl-model))
            (fca-ask question)
            (fca-fallback-answer question)))

    0)
